meta.title: Market Psychology Map: Semantic News Clusters

inspector.description: Uses OpenAI Embeddings + t-SNE (Dimensionality Reduction) to map 1,536 dimensions of news context into 2D space. Bubbles are colored by Market Impact (Bull Trap vs Justified Optimism). Filters applied: 7-Day Rolling Window, Signal-only Sentiment (>0.1).
inspector.sql_logic:
SELECT 
    news_id,
    ticker,
    title,
    published_at,
    x,
    y,
    cluster_id,
    sentiment,
    impact,
    label
FROM STOCKS_ELT_DB.MARTS.MRT_MASSIVE__NEWS_CLUSTERS
WHERE 
    x IS NOT NULL
    -- 1. Recency Filter: Keep map fresh (Rolling 7 Day Window)
    AND published_at >= DATEADD('day', -7, CURRENT_DATE())
    -- 2. Sentiment Intensity: Remove "Grey" neutral news (Signal-to-Noise)
    AND ABS(sentiment) >= 0.1
ORDER BY published_at DESC
LIMIT 1000
inspector.dbt_logic:
-- 1. PYTHON CALCULATION LAYER (models/intermediate/int_massive__snowpark_news_clusters.py)
# Calculates Geometry Only (X/Y/Cluster) using OpenAI Embeddings + t-SNE
def model(dbt, session):
    dbt.config(materialized="table", packages=["pandas", "scikit-learn", "numpy"])
    
    # Load Embeddings
    df = dbt.ref("int_massive__news_cluster_prep").to_pandas()
    matrix = np.stack(df['SUMMARY_EMBEDDING'].values)

    # Run t-SNE (1536 dims -> 2 dims)
    tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, perplexity=30, random_state=42)
    projections = tsne.fit_transform(matrix)

    # Run K-Means (Topic Detection)
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=8, random_state=42)
    clusters = kmeans.fit_predict(matrix)

    # Return Map Data (Slim)
    df['X_COORD'] = projections[:, 0]
    df['Y_COORD'] = projections[:, 1]
    df['CLUSTER_ID'] = clusters
    
    return df[['NEWS_ID', 'X_COORD', 'Y_COORD', 'CLUSTER_ID', 'NARRATIVE_LABEL']]

-- 2. MART INTERFACE (models/marts/mrt_massive__news_clusters.sql)
# Joins Geometry back to Text Context and Seed Metadata
WITH map_data AS ( SELECT * FROM {{ ref('int_massive__snowpark_news_clusters') }} ),
text_data AS ( SELECT news_id, ticker, title, published_at, sentiment_score FROM {{ ref('int_massive__market_news') }} ),
seed_tickers AS ( SELECT ticker, category, sector FROM {{ ref('stocks_tickers') }} )

SELECT 
    t1.news_id,
    t2.ticker,
    t2.title,
    t2.published_at,
    t1.x_coord as x,
    t1.y_coord as y,
    t1.cluster_id,
    t2.sentiment_score as sentiment,
    t1.narrative_label as label
FROM map_data t1
JOIN text_data t2 ON t1.news_id = t2.news_id

  - name: mrt_massive__news_clusters
    description: >
      [VIEW]: The Public API for the Market Psychology Map.
      Joins the calculated coordinates (Python) with the actual text/metadata (SQL).
    columns:
      - name: x
        description: "X-Axis Coordinate (t-SNE)."
      - name: y
        description: "Y-Axis Coordinate (t-SNE)."
      - name: cluster_id
        description: "Topic Cluster Group (0-7)."
